# Plan Eval (Rubric) — AdvertEyes Improve Pass (plan-eval2)

## Context

Improve pass: original plan passed all rubric gates (plan-eval.out VERDICT: pass). planner2.out is a surgical delta — no new features, no design changes, no tech changes. Evaluating only the delta plan's changes against rubric gates.

## Rubric Assessment

### 1. Requirements coverage

All original requirements remain covered (unchanged from plan-eval.out). The delta adds:
- Auth fallback with 4 hard-coded demo users (admin/sales/ops/client roles) — ensures RBAC demo survives API downtime
- No requirements removed or regressed

The improve pass does not reduce richness or drop any feature. ✓

### 2. Technology choices

No new tech introduced. Auth fallback uses:
- Base64-encoded mock JWT (`demo.` prefix) — simple, browser-native, zero new deps
- `OFFLINE_MODE` flag in existing `api/index.ts` — no new files, no new libs

Correct approach: simpler than adding an offline-first library; fully reversible. ✓

### 3. Testing approach

- Playwright deploy-test will re-run against live after deploy (deploy-test2)
- Auth fallback is exercised by any login attempt with seeded credentials — no special test hook needed
- Surface port check is done during demo-builder2 via surface runner (explicit 3741 verification)

Sufficient. ✓

### 4. Scope feasibility at richness 10/10

Delta is ~30 lines in one file (`api/index.ts`) + `npm run build` + git staging. Estimated demo-builder2 time: under 15 minutes. No risk of scope creep.

Feature richness at 10/10 is already fully delivered by the existing build — this pass restores access to it. ✓

### 5. Design direction fit for industry

Unaffected. Original design (dark navy + billboard orange, Barlow Condensed, OOH data-dense ops aesthetic) is already built. ✓

